SUMMARY:Spring Taste of Bird-in-Hand
DESCRIPTION:Sample the sweet\, sour\, savory goodness of our kitchens \nStop by the tasting event at our Artisan Village to sample a variety of the products from Bird-in-Hand following traditional and family recipes. You’ll also be able to taste food from the local purveyors represented in our Village Pantry section. \nDate: Saturday\, April 11\nTime: 10 a.m. – 4 p.m.
URL:https://bird-in-hand.com/event/spring-taste-of-bird-in-hand/
LOCATION:Bird-in-Hand Artisan Village\, 2705 Old Philadelphia Pike\, Bird-in-Hand\, PA\, 17505\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bird-in-hand.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/TasteofBIHHeaderImage-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Bird-in-Hand
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260513
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260514
DTSTAMP:20260410T225211
CREATED:20260204T175912Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260204T175912Z
UID:10001052-1778630400-1778716799@bird-in-hand.com
SUMMARY:Farm to Fork Experience
DESCRIPTION:Real Farms • Real Food\nMay 13\, 2026\nFood doesn’t get any more authentic than Bird-in-Hand’s Farm-to-Fork Experience. From milking cows to making ice cream to growing chemical-free produce from seed\, you’ll meet Mennonite and Amish farmers and get an intimate view of how Lancaster County’s bounty begins. Our own John Smucker\, an eighth-generation farmer\, will be your guide on this unforgettable experience\, which culminates in a mouth-watering farm-to-fork meal. \nThe Farm to Fork Experience package includes:\n• Two-night stay in the historic Bird-in-Hand Village Inn & Suites\n• Tours of local farms and a lunch made with ingredients from our tour – see itinerary below\n• Daily deluxe continental breakfasts for two at the Village Inn & Suites or credit at the Bird-in-Hand Bakery & Cafe\n• Dinner for two at the Bird-in-Hand Family Restaurant & Smorgasbord on Tuesday or Wednesday\n• Welcome market basket filled with local foods \nSpace is limited so reserve early. Enjoy this package for $585 (plus tax). Extend your stay for only $109 a night (plus tax). For more information on the Village Inn & Suites\, click here. Walking is required for these tours. \nRequires $200 deposit to reserve your tour (refundable up to two weeks prior to event). $109 extra night available for any room type. Taxes not included. \n  \n2026 TOUR ITINERARY \nRise\, Shine & Dine (5:30 am): Wake up with the roosters and see cows being milked at our neighbor Aaron Lantz’s organic farm. Then savor a delicious farm-fresh breakfast with the Lantz family in their kitchen. \nHydroponic Farming: At Millcreek Hydroponics\, we’ll learn about the sustainable year-round growing methods for their lettuce and microgreens\, and tour their greenhouse. \nThe Time is Ripe: Take an orchard tour of Kauffman’s Fruit & Farm Market and learn how they produce their apple cider. \nVeggies on the Vine: Amish farmer Ephraim Huyard will show us his biological methods of growing plants\, and how he grows the chemical-free vegetable plants. \nGrowing Green: Meet Wesley Groff\, third-generation farmer of Groff’s Celery and Vegetable Farm\, and learn how he grows crops from seed in a chemical-free environment. \nGrown Local Luncheon: You’ve seen where it’s grown. Now taste the fresh difference. Receive a market basket of local foods after lunch. \nSave Room for Dessert: Our last stop after lunch will be a visit to the Bird-in-Hand Bakery & Cafe\, where we make our artisan ice cream.
URL:https://bird-in-hand.com/event/farm-to-fork-experience/
LOCATION:Bird-in-Hand Village Inn & Suites\, 2695 Old Philadelphia Pike\, Bird-in-Hand\, PA\, 17505\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bird-in-hand.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/2017FarmFreshHeader1.jpg
GEO:40.0387462;-76.1799845
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Bird-in-Hand Village Inn & Suites 2695 Old Philadelphia Pike Bird-in-Hand PA 17505 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=2695 Old Philadelphia Pike:geo:-76.1799845,40.0387462
END:VEVENT
